  "label::qa_definition": "",
  "label::qa_factoid": "Covers questions asking for a specific fact about a person, place, or thing, where the expected answer is a concrete piece of information (such as a birthdate, height, or one-time event). If unsure between 'qa_factoid' and 'general_quirky', choose 'qa_factoid' only when the input clearly asks for a direct, factual answer; otherwise, use 'general_quirky' for more open-ended or broad queries.",
  "label::qa_stock": "",
  "label::recommendation_events": "",
  "label::recommendation_locations": "Covers requests for actionable suggestions of specific places, venues, or destinations to visit, typically framed as asking where to go, what places to try, or for recommendations of locations. Only use this label when the input directly asks for places to visit or experience, not for opinions about the \"best\" or most interesting place—assign such opinion-based prompts to 'general_quirky'.",
